caption: Whole foods place located on the corner of 117th. A salad is about 12 dollars. Several hot patty options and plated entree options. Sea moss shakes. Currently you have to order take out through a window. Short wait.

Great small business in Harlem operated by men of color. HEALTH FOOD is what you will find here. Popular place in the community to find healthy wraps, patties, hot food plates, fresh juice and smoothies, libido tonics for men. Clean, as well as excellent service. If you are vegan or vegetarian, you will definitely find something here you will enjoy that caters to your life style.

Small harlem food shop. Multiple vegan/vegetarian options, but also has meat options, hot food (rice/quinoa base), salads, wraps, fruit smoothies. I had some kind of seasoned tofu with purple cabbage, chickpeas, and some vegetable stuff, on a brown rice base, which tasted excellent - delicious flavour/spices, and more than enough for one person. I got the small option for 9$, but the larger portion is 12 or 13$.  Not much space to sit as the store is quite small (maybe enough space for 5-6 people) but theres a park nearby, or central park a few blocks down. Only thing I didnt like was the "Hals" BBQ chips, they werent the best (almost felt like they had no seasoning) but its not like they make the chips, so just stock different ones I guess! Overall this was an excellent place, especially for vegan food, and I will definitely be back.

I was looking around for a good salad spot and came across this one because of the reviews on Google. I ordered a mixed green salad with spicy chicken and it was DELICIOUS!  The service was also great!  It's not an ideal eat-in place but its perfect for a quick bite if you're hungry and on the run. They have a small table and a few stools to sit on.
